name: Craig Robins
bio:
CEO of Dacra @MiamiDesignDistrict
Chairman & Co-Founder @DesignMiami
Art & Design Collector
Philanthropist

social_posts.post_text: Day one is in the books. Lovely to see so many friends at Art Basel and Design Miami yesterday.

We had a great time celebrating the opening of my collection “Two of the Same Kind” along with the Gagosian x Deitch “100 Years” opening. But the true star of the night was my mom. Thank you to all those who came.

Saatchi Yates Gallery has a beautiful exhibition in the Design District featuring @tesfayeurgessa. 

35 NE 40th Street
Austin Millz came to mix on top of Museum Garage.

Pleased to welcome such exciting shows to the District. 

Daniel Arsham presenting The Ares House 

Art in Common presenting Boil + Toil 

Josué Thomas presenting Work in Progress
Design Miami by night.

A true fashion night out in Design District. 

Domenico Dolce in the Dolce & Gabbana Casa pop up

Mr. Lobutin hosting a soirée at the Christian Lobutin boutique 

Gaetano Pesce visiting the “Ciao Bottega: Come Stai?” Exhibit for a book signing.
Monday after Basel.
We now bring you Breakfast at Tiffany’s.
@gallerydepartment rocks. Featuring Barkley Hendricks.
Killing time with @chaosursfischer

There is a disco ball in Jade Alley. 

As part of this years design commission, Germane Barnes has taken over the neighborhood with his installation Rock|Roll.
@nodaleto has landed in the District. Help @julia_nodaleto pick out what pair to wear in her first flagship store.
Jackie knows how to get me going. We had a wonderful holiday party for all of our companies.

Wishing everyone a merry Christmas and a wonderful holiday.
Gone skiing.

Ready to drop into 2023. Happy new year to all.
New Year. Same partner. I am a lucky man.
Hard to believe this was a decade ago. Explaining our vision for Palm Court. Feeling so much gratitude to all those who came together to make this place a reality.
Beautiful day in the neighborhood. @amiri
I am going back to school.
South Beach boys. My brother Scott and I in front of the Webster Hotel. We bought this piece of art deco history together and made it our home through most of the 90’s.

This year's jerseys in support of the Dolphin Challenge will be coming out soon. You should definitely try to sign up. It supports cancer research at the University of Miami. 

The jerseys featured are designed by Harmony Korine for the 2020 @dolphinschallengecancer.
Four best friends heading to @chanelofficial.
The LV Flagship glows in the dark.
Wearing @tomford with Tom Ford Chairman Domenico De Sole and my beautiful wife.
The Reverend Martin Luther King pictured at Hampton House Miami. We have come a long way as a city and a country since this photo was taken, but we still have a long way to go.
Bottega Veneta pop-up on the Paseo.
Parisian taste reigns supreme. Even with umbrellas.

Chaz Michael Michaels is floored as Urs Fischer keeps the looks coming.

Well this is new…
Do you think Jackie will be my date for Concours this year?
A McQueen taxi and best dressed couple of the day enjoying the gt2P swing.
A living Yayoi Kusama spotted in LV.
Phaidon x Women Made dinner at my house with guest of honor Solange Knowles. 2021.
Design Miami 2020 at the Moore. Jason Jaques Gallery presented two nearly complete Camptosaurus and Allosaurus dinosaur skeletons excavated from Wyoming.
A polaroid portrait of my wonderful mother taken by Andy Warhol.
What a day.
A very big celebrity sighting in the office. Jana Euler's slug is taking a seat in our lobby.
Mr. Glickenhaus and I are ready for this year's Concours. See you all on President's Day weekend.
Our performance series in Palm Court were legendary. Mambo Babalu in 2018. Can’t wait for the MISO concert at The Moore next week.
Forever Valentine.
Incredible when one of the best people on the planet teams up with one of the very best brands. Congratulations Pharrell and Louis Vuitton. The Great Virgil must be smiling.

I have a stunt double today. Thank you for all the well wishes. 

The painting to my left is “End of Christianity” by Marlene Dumas.
Taking something unattractive and making it beautiful. Artist Antony Marest came to the District to paint over a messy wall under the Fendi Facade. Anything can be art.
Red carpet day is here. Don’t miss todays show.
We are always up to something. Can't wait for tonight. Thank you Emilio.
A magical night. Thank you to our dear friends @emilioestefanjr and @eduardomarturet for this celebration of The Moore.
Major news: Kith and Kith Treats are opening tomorrow in the neighborhood. Can't wait for you all to check it out.

Daniel Arsham does it again. Custom Rapha jerseys for the MDD Team riding in this year's Dolphin Challenge. Thank you for all your support and can't wait to ride tomorrow. All proceeds go to cancer research at Sylvester, University of Miami.
There are no Monday blues in our offices.
Looking back at South Beach Wine and Food Festival celebrations in Jungle Plaza. My diet starts today.

How do you translate a vision into identity and then identity into a brand capable of uniting a community?

Both a creative neighbourhood and luxury shopping destination, @miamidesigndistrict is a placemaking icon. Dedicated to innovative fashion, art, design and dining, it is an ever-evolving cultural hub. When creating the brand identity, it was clear to Made Thought that creative bravery was not just optional. 

As we reflect on the creative partnership–now over a decade in the making–our founding partner Paul Austin sits down with MDD’s founder Craig Robins. They discuss what it means to capture a sense of place and how to evoke lasting impact in today’s creative sphere.

Visit the link in bio to watch the film.
All that glitters is not gold. Sometimes it is a Reclining Mermaid. A stunning new installation by Elliot & Erick Jiménez on the Moore building.
It’s always a party when Emily Estefan is on stage. She will be back at Palm Court on November 7th at 7:30PM. Please join us.

It is always an honor to share the stage with you @emilioestefanjr. Thank you @estefanialacayo @samanthatams @sandracamposnyc for creating such a special panel for Emilio and I to be a part of. Another great year of LAFS in the Miami Design District.
LAFS has truly become an incredible time of year for Miami and the Design District. Each year is better than the last. We can’t wait to see what next year holds.
Emily rocks Palm Court.

We had the privilege of presenting the prototype of this concept at the inaugural Design Miami/ Paris fair earlier in the fall. Now there are 12 benches installed throughout the Design District for all to enjoy. Congratulations to the Samuel Ross Design team.

I have officially been immortalized. We cannot wait to celebrate JR’s incredible homage to Miami, tonight. Featuring a special performance by @anitta in Jungle Plaza. Come one, come all.

Together LVMH, the Miami Design District and Florida Power and Light are stepping towards a more sustainable future. Through this partnership, we are so proud to announce that the  Design District will be a carbon neutral neighborhood in 2024. Thank you Jane for mediating such a wonderful panel with Pamela Rauch, Anish Melwani and me to present this exciting initiative.

I have a VERY special announcement. David Chipperfield has been retained to design the West End of the neighborhood. This will include a five star boutique hotel, condos and luxury retail. Almost a year ago a partnership between Raycliff Capital, Fort Partners, Constellation Hotels Holding and Miami Design District Associates acquired 15 buildings on the West End of the Miami Design District. 
 
We cannot wait to get to work.
